 <title xml:id="NetworkServices">Disable DNS</title>
 <para>
  Disables the Domain Name System (DNS), which is used to translate
  numerical IP addresses into human-readable machine names.
  <indexterm>
   <primary>DNS</primary>
  </indexterm>
 </para>
 <para>
  Most machines in an organization do not need a DNS server running.
  Unless this machine is one of the organizationâ€™s name servers, it is
  safe to disable this service.
 </para>
